
Audio Engine
============

A audio synth engine aimed at retro games. Sound is defined in patterns and 
can be queued up on multiple channels.



To use
======

Copy files starting with audio- into your project, add them to your build
system and add port audio as library dependency. Then initialize, define
your beepy beeps and play then back. See main.cc for example.



Requires
- port audio
- SDL for demo



Features

- port audio backend (could be ported to any simple sound API, like SDL or alsa)
- different wave forms (sine, square, noise, saw, triangle)
- volume and pitch configurable for each tone
- multiple channels can play sounds independently
- per channel looped playback

